body:
Some additional information.
The issue occurs with string#match, but not string#scan.  Also, since the issue occurs in 1.9.3 but not 2.0 I did a diff of the 1.9.3 string#match with the 2.0 string#match, the snippet of the difference is below:
I'm not sure what `rb_check_arity` does, but maybe it provides some clue as to what's going on.

1.9.3

```
if (argc < 1)
    rb_check_arity(argc, 1, 2);
re = argv[0];
```

2.0

```
if (argc < 1)
   rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "wrong number of arguments (%d for 1..2)", argc);
re = argv[0];
```
